The paper discusses the design of legs for a hexapod robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Bezier splines and CPPN-NEAT suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The comparison of performance across different environments involves machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques.
